•	

Restructuring the idea of 
‘value’ in Real Estate 
Development – the 
‘both/and’ condition 
Value  in real estate 
development has often been 
focused on quick monetary 
gain. However, through 
approaching this project 
through layering and 
incorporating feedback 
mechanisms to guide design 
over time, we can begin to 
develop value in many more 
areas including: the building of 
social capital, ensuring public 
amenity and the continued 
rehabilitation of the site. 
•	 We also hope to prove that 
through working in this way, the 
long-term monetary gains will 
be greater than short-term 
profits. 

